G√•r man til audition inden for sang og bliver udtaget til koret blandt rollerne/ensemblet, synger man med p√• mange af de 24 numre i forestillingen ud over at indg√• i mange af de komiske indslag og scener undervejs.

ANG√ÖENDE ROLLER:
N√•r der √•bnes op for auditiontilmeldinger medio december, kan man l√¶se alt om de individuelle roller i forestillingen samt hvad man skal forberede, hvis man g√•r op p√• en rolle eller som ensemble. G√•r man op til ensemblet udelukkende som danser (uden at ville synge eller have replikker i forestillingen), vil man ikke skulle forberede noget hjemmefra. 

ANG√ÖENDE FORESTILLINGEN:
G√∏r dig klar til et latter-festbrag uden lige og glem alt, hvad du tror du ved om musicals ‚Äì og riddere! "SPAMALOT" er baseret p√• den komiske filmklassiker "Monty Python og de sk√∏re riddere" fra 1975 og kaster dig direkte ind i et vanvittigt middelaldereventyr fyldt med latter, kokosn√∏dder, uendelige forvirringer og totalt meningsl√∏se heltebedrifter! 
Forestillingen f√∏lger Kong Arthur og hans noget alternative Riddere af Det Runde Bord, som begiver sig ud p√• en b√•de farlig, t√•belig og fuldst√¶ndig absurd jagt efter Den Hellige Gral. Undervejs m√∏der de alt fra franske forn√¶rmelser til dansende munke, en dr√¶berkanin, dansenymfer, flyvende k√∏er ‚Äì og ikke mindst en vaske√¶gte musicaldiva med stort D!
Der er satire, sk√∏re jokes samt catchy sange og dansenumre i overflod (hvem kan ikke huske "Always Look on the Bright Side of Life"?) i et festfyrv√¶rkeri af b√•de en hyldest til og parodi af musicalgenren. Det er uforudsigeligt, ufiltreret og helt ustyrligt morsomt. En skaml√∏st vidunderlig teateroplevelse for fans af Broadway-musicals og af Monty Pythons forrygende humor ‚Äì og alle dem, der snart bliver det!
"SPAMALOT" har de seneste tyve √•r haft sin sejrsgang over hele verden og blev efter sin debut p√• Broadway i 2005 nomineret til hele 14 Tony-priser og vandt blandt andet for √Örets Bedste Musical. Det bliver med garanti en uforglemmelig og ridderligt underholdende sommer i 2026 ‚Äì for b√•de publikum og de medvirkende!
Nyborg Voldspils ops√¶tning af ‚ÄùSPAMALOT‚Äù er den f√∏rste udend√∏rsopf√∏rsel af forestillingen p√• Fyn nogensinde og instrueres af Rasmus Mansachs, der tidligere har instrueret de to ‚ÄùVi maler byen r√∏d: The Musical‚Äù-ops√¶tninger i henholdsvis 2021 og 2025. K√∏b billetter til ‚ÄùSPAMALOT‚Äù allerede nu her: nyborgvoldspil.dk

AUDITIONTILMELDING:
Der √•bnes op for tilmeldinger medio december 2025. Audition finder sted d. 10.-11. januar 2026. Det vil blive meldt ud p√• Nyborg Voldspils Facebook- og Instagram-profiler, s√• snart man kan tilmelde sig og l√¶se mere om de individuelle roller, ensemblet og selve pr√∏veplanen. Vi ses til auditon!

Tonight and tomorrow only at No Square Theatre in Laguna Beach!

Get your tickets at: [https://www.tix.com/ticket-sales/nosquare/1804](https://www.tix.com/ticket-sales/nosquare/1804?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExdE9CMUlNdmlWaHQ1Z0hXRHNydGMGYXBwX2lkDzUxNDc3MTU2OTIyODA2MQABHhigjsOFZIS1vnXu10jY_YsHWJ5nXvz5lgiqWRc5_TvZ_pxZxMayZs6Vc-tX_aem_Qgp-5aGk8mHoi59iA-L5bQ)

SHE KILLS MONSTERS: YOUNG ADVENTURERS EDITION, a play by Qui Nguyen and directed by No Square Theatre Artistic Director, Joe Lauderdale, tells the story of high schooler Agnes Evans as she deals with the death of her younger sister, Tilly. When Agnes finds Tilly‚Äôs Dungeons & Dragons notebook, she gets pulled into an exciting adventure in the imaginary world that was her sister‚Äôs escape. The story is a thrilling, fast-paced dramatic comedy laden with homicidal fairies, nasty ogres, and ‚Äô90s pop culture celebrating both the geek and the warrior inside all of us.

November 22 & 23 Only!

items.text:
DAHLONEGA- Short Film- Auditions Open! 
Local Talent!
Unpaid-IMDB credited

Auditions happen NOW! for the first film of the season: ‚ÄúTHE SHAPE OF GOODBYE‚Äù

DEADLINE: Jan. 4th

An adaptation of the amazing play written by the talented John Mabey. 

All you have to do is email a video link of a 1-2 minute dramatic monologue to

fofingerfilmsauditions@gmail.com

Here is the Character list: 

MARCUS (30-45) stoic, disciplined, carrying unspoken grief
YOUNG MARCUS (17-21)- introspective, sensitive, with a youthful vulnerability
DUSTIN (45-60) - strong, confident, with a commanding presence
BOYFRIEND (17-21) - charming, caring, with a playful yet earnest demeanor
 HUSBAND (30-45) - loyal, contlicted, balancing love and responsibility
 MOTHER (35-45) - nurturing, resilient, emotionally grounded

Film summary 
THE SHAPE OF GOODBYE: 
FOLLOWS A FATHER AND SON
AS THEY STRUGGLE TO CONNECT
OF IN THEIR FRACTURED RELATIONSHIP ACROSS TIME. THROUGH GRIEF, LOVE AND HUMOR, THEY FIGHT THEIR WAY TOWARD HEALING AND TO EACH OTHER. AND WHAT THEY DISCOVER ALONG THE WAY FRACTURES
THE SHAPE OF TIME ITSELF AS MEMORIES
BECOME MANIFEST AND REVEAL UNSPOKEN TRUTHS.

FILMING DATES:

JAN. 31,FEB. 1st, and FEB, 7th and 8th
(subject to change)

WHERE: 
DAHLONEGA, GA

NON-PAID, IMDb CREDIT INCLUDED

Good luck! Message if you have any questions. We will gladly help you!

FO FINGER FILMS.

MARCUS (30-45) stoic, disciplined, carrying unspoken grief
YOUNG MARCUS (17-21)- introspective, sensitive, with a youthful vulnerability
DUSTIN (45-60) - strong, confident, with a commanding presence
BOYFRIEND (17-21) - charming, caring, with a playful yet earnest demeanor
 HUSBAND (30-45) - loyal, contlicted, balancing love and responsibility
 MOTHER (35-45) - nurturing, resilient, emotionally grounded

Film summary 
THE SHAPE OF GOODBYE: 
FOLLOWS A FATHER AND SON
AS THEY STRUGGLE TO CONNECT
OF IN THEIR FRACTURED RELATIONSHIP ACROSS TIME. THROUGH GRIEF, LOVE AND HUMOR, THEY FIGHT THEIR WAY TOWARD HEALING AND TO EACH OTHER. AND WHAT THEY DISCOVER ALONG THE WAY FRACTURES
THE SHAPE OF TIME ITSELF AS MEMORIES
BECOME MANIFEST AND REVEAL UNSPOKEN TRUTHS.

FILMING DATES:

JAN. 31,FEB. 1st, and FEB, 7th and 8th
(subject to change)

WHERE: 
DAHLONEGA, GA

NON-PAID, IMDb CREDIT INCLUDED

Good luck! Message if you have any questions. We will gladly help you!

FO FINGER FILMS.

items.text:
Role Type: Supporting Gender: Male Age Range: Early to mid-20s Ethnicity: African American Build: Tall, physically imposing preferred

 Character Description:

 Dre is loud, cocky, and always looking to prove himself ‚Äî even when no one‚Äôs watching. He‚Äôs the type to stir the pot just for the reaction. A natural bully with a chip on his shoulder, Gangster Type. He‚Äôs a knucklehead with presence ‚Äî the guy you hear before you see. Seeking an actor with strong physicality and comedic or dramatic timing to bring Dre‚Äôs over-the-top bravado to life.

GRANDMA B Role Type: Supporting / Featured Gender: Female Age Range: Late 60s to 70s Ethnicity: African American, Mixed Race, or Hispanic Build: Average height and build.

 Character Description:

 Grandma B is the rock of the family ‚Äî wise, resilient, and sharp as ever. She speaks her mind with no filter and delivers truth with wit and love. Strong in her faith and unshakable in her values, she‚Äôs as quick with a Bible verse as she is with a one-liner. Whether offering tough love or quiet comfort, she‚Äôs always ten steps ahead. Looking for a seasoned actress who can bring warmth, sass, and soul to this memorable matriarch. 

 Roylina

Female25-40 y.o.

Latino / Hispanic

Character Description: 

Roylina is a powerful Mafia Boss‚Äîcommanding, strategic, and captivating. She carries herself with confidence, intensity, and an air of danger. The actress must be able to portray strength, authority, and emotional depth.

JACOB (JAY) -

Type: Principal

Gender: Male

Age Range: Early to mid-20s

Ethnicity: African American or Mixed Race

Complexion: Brown to Light

Build: Tall, athletic

 

Character Description:

Jacob (Jay) is confident, grounded, and carries a quiet strength. He‚Äôs sharp, emotionally mature beyond his years, and physically active. Jay‚Äôs presence is felt even in silence ‚Äì calm but commanding. His past has shaped him, but he doesn‚Äôt wear it on his sleeve. Looking for an actor who can bring both vulnerability and strength to the role with authenticity and nuance.

Check out this teaser trailer for a future Batman film project expecting to film in the near future. ü¶á üìΩÔ∏è 

Vagabond Pictures

sharedPost.text: We filmed this teaser trailer for a potential Batman film project a number of years ago at Bangor Marina, County Down. Titled "A Meeting of Two Minds" this film would have followed the young up-and-coming Commissioner Gordon who is tasked with his first major case in Gotham; to find the culprit behind the kidnapping of the Mayor's son. It would have explored numerous origin stories including a young Harvey Dent and even The Joker's father. This psychological thriller is still very much a work in progress for a film in the near future.

items.text:
Casting Call!

We have one role left to cast!!

*Starchild* is a sci-fi drama that follows the story of two scientists, Vanessa and Tanner as they take separate paths to deal with their grief. Vanessa through faith, and Tanner through science. It's not until they discover the origins of life itself, that they reconcile to start a family of their own.

Looking to cast supporting character John Marlow.

The film is heartfelt, honest, and powerful.

Please send resume, headshot, and (if applicable) demo reel to starchildcasting@gmail.com

attachments.ocrText: May be a graphic of text that says 'STARCHILD Casting Call! 1CHARACTERSSTILLAVAILIBLE! 1CHARACTER STILL AVAILIBLE!! LOOKING FOR: MALE SUPPORTING CHARACTER MALE-SUPPORTINGCHARACTER- 30'S 30'S-60'S 60'S EMAIL BELOW FOR SUBMISSION DETAILS STARCHILDCASTING@GMAIL.COM'
May be an image of text

May be an image of text that says 'John Marlowe Male Late 30s to 60s Any ethnicity Pastor John carries quiet authority and compassion, arriving with coffee, donuts, and genuine care. He sees through Tanner's defenses in single conversation and challenges him to grieve with honesty his faith grounded in realism. Though a one- scene role, his presence anchors the story's moral compass, bridging belief and understanding. Must bring warmth, presence, and strong listening skills.'

items.text: Was meint Ihr? Ist die Angst vor einer Nichtbuchung berechtigt?

sharedPost.text:
+++ ANGST vor Nichtbuchung bei Kritik +++

Ein heikles Thema, was immerwieder f√ºr Konflikte, aber  auch oft f√ºr Missverst√§ndnisse sorgt.

Dazu zwei typische Zitate aus unseren Kontakten:

"Ich hab da einmal wegen einer Zulage nachgefragt und dann abgesagt. Seitdem werde ich da nicht mehr gebucht."

"Ich frag da lieber nicht nach und mach den Dreh mit schlechter Gage, dann bekomm ich da auch wieder bessere  Sachen."

So, oder so √§hnlich h√∂ren wir ab und an von Filmschaffenden  berichtet.

Obwohl es sich hierbei erstmal nur um Ger√ºchte handelt f√§llt uns doch auf, dass dieser Glaube an diese traurige  Konsequenz der Agenturen, Booker und Caster  (selbst im Bereich der einfachsten  Komparserie) sehr
verbreitet ist.

Dazu haben wir durch unsere √ºber 10-j√§hrige  Erfahrung und  Eure, uns vielen anvertrauten PN,s aber auch ganz einfach durch unsere vielen Beitrags-Statistiken ein  eindeutiges Ergebnis:

Die Angst, bereits nur bei sachlich, netter und geringf√ºgiger Kritik, nicht gebucht zu werden ist auch in unserem Arbeitsbereich Komparserie, Kleindarstellerei ein unbestrittener Fakt und sehr verbreitet. 

Nur ein aktuelles Beispiel:

Unser letzter Beitrag zum  Unmut einer √§u√üerst gro√üen deutschen Produktionsst√§tte hatte auch eine besonders starke Leserschaft Jedoch sind die Reaktionen  unserer Leserschaft auf unserer Kritik und sogar unsere erzielten Erfolge bei  den gro√üen Playern wesenlich geringer als bei kleineren  Produktionen oder unseren allgemein geltenden  Artikeln.

Aber woher kommt diese zumindest allgemein sicherlich unbegr√ºndete Angst?

Dazu schauen wir in unsere unz√§hligen vertraulichen PNs, und auch dort ist immerwieder die Angst ein exorbitanter Faktor.
Dort und auch bei unseren Gespr√§chen an unseren Infost√§nden aber auch in den Aufenthaltsr√§umen der Drehorte h√∂rt man einen recht h√§ufigen Schlusssatz: 
"Aber Psst, sonst werde ich da nicht mehr gebucht"

Die pers√∂nlichen Erfahrungen unserer  Redaktion (Claudia und Klaus) aber auch von anderen, uns √∂ffentlich unterst√ºtzenden Filmschaffenden sprechen dagegen eine ganz andere Sprache.

Obwohl sehr viele  Produktionen und Agenturen unsere  √∂ffentliche Kritik und uns damit auch namentlich kennen, hatten wir dadurch nie das Problem einer systematischen Nichtbuchung zu beklagen. 

Dies erscheint uns auch als v√∂llig logisch, denn erfahrungsgem√§√ü haben Agenturen, Casting und Regie gar nicht die Zeit f√ºr eine zeitraubende Differenzierung - zumindest im Bereich Komparserie aber auch bei Kleindarstellerrollen.

Das hei√üt nat√ºrlich nicht, dass auch  wir  mal mit den Konditionen einer Produktion o. Agentur bez√ºglich unserer pers√∂nlichen Buchungen  immer ganz einig waren und daher auch einfach mal "nein" gesagt haben.

Daher k√∂nnen wir auch m√∂gliche systematisch angewendeten "schwarze Listen" aufgrund unserer umfangreichen Informationen, weitestgehend nicht best√§tigen. 

So hatten wir eigentlich nur in einem Fall  der Vergangenheit leider mehrere Hinweise darauf, dass bereits der Kontakt zu unserer Initiative zum  Ausschluss aus der Kartei f√ºhren w√ºrde. 

Wir hoffen aber, dass diese sehr traurigen, uns vorliegenden Drohungen an Filmschaffende aktuell dort und nat√ºrlich auch insgesamt nicht praktiziert werden.
Im Einzelfall gibt es sicherlich auch mal Konflikte, die jedoch im pers√∂nlichen und m√∂glichst freundlichen Austausch auf Augenh√∂he schnell beseitigt werden sollten.

Was wir letztendlich jedoch nicht ausschlie√üen k√∂nnen, ist eine andere Art der Nichtbuchung.
Diese ist gar nicht so selten und beschreibt den Fall einer  Bevorzugung eines sogenannten "Komparsenpools" der zumindest  h√§ufigere Buchungen erf√§hrt  als Menschen, die vielleicht  nicht (oder noch nicht) zum Kreis der √∂fter gebuchten Filmschaffenden geh√∂ren. 

Auch hier berichten uns jedoch die meisten Agenturen, dass hier keinesfalls die "alten Hasen" bevorzugt werden. 
Zudem handelt es sich beim Buchungsprocedere ja nur um mehrere Vorschl√§ge aus einer Kartei, die der Regieassistenz  vorgelegt werden oder die Produktion hat bereits selbst den Zugriff auf die   Kartei. So bestimmt die eigentliche Auswahl der gebuchten Filmgesichter fast immer die Regieassistenz oder auch direkt die Regie.

Dazu geh√∂rt auch die sogenannte Stammkomparserie in der Serienproduktion. Auch hier  entsteht oft der Eindruck einer Bevorzugung.
Dieser Umstand ist jedoch erstmal nachvollziebar, wenn eine √∂fter genutzte Hintergrund-Location einen Erkennungswert bei der Serienproduktion fordert (z.B. Dorfbewohner, Krankenhauspersonal, Polizeib√ºro oder auch die "Spusi-Chlique").

+++ So k√∂nnen wir auch bez√ºglich unserer eigenen Erfahrungen, nur immerwieder dazu appellieren, auch mehrfach wiederholte  Absagen nicht pers√∂nlich zu nehmen +++

Nichtsdestotrotz wollen wir an dieser Stelle gern alle Agenturen und Produktionen freundlich bitten, auch weiterhin eine gesunde Mischung, alter wie neuer Gesichter der Regie vorzuschlagen um auch allen  Filmschaffenden m√∂glichst gleiche Buchungschancen zu gew√§hrleisten. Dies gilt nat√ºrlich ganz Insbesonders  bei den wenigen Pay-Agenturen.

Abschlie√üend  k√∂nnen wir nur nochmal beruhigend res√ºmieren: 

+++ Bez√ºglich recht verbreiteter √Ñngste vor einer Nichtbuchung  sehen wir f√ºr unseren   Arbeitsbereich keinerlei Gr√ºnde, sich mit sachlich und freundlich gef√ºhrter Kritik bei den Verantwortlichen oder eben hier bei Faire Gagen sich mit kritischen Meinungen zur√ºckzuhalten. 
Also nur Mut zur Kritik. Insgesamt gesehen haben wir da absolut nichts zu verlieren +++

Wir sehen uns als Sprachrohr f√ºr alle Filmschaffenden, Agenturen und Produktionen. Gerne nehmen wir dazu Eure Erfahrungen und Beispiele und damit nat√ºrlich auch die der Agenturen und Produktionen gleich hier auf Faire Gagen auch via PN mit in die Diskussion.
 
Redaktion Faire Gagen: Claudia Raquet u.Klaus Stutzer 

(Artikel, Foto: K. Stutzer)

CASTING CALL ‚Äì MALE LEAD (UNPAID, STUDENT FILM)
Hi everyone! I‚Äôm currently casting for a student short horror film and we‚Äôre looking for someone to play the primary antagonist ‚Äî a cannibalistic butcher in a dark, atmospheric short.

Role Requirements:
 ‚Ä¢ Male, age 30‚Äì50
 ‚Ä¢ Tall and stocky build
 ‚Ä¢ No dialogue required ‚Äî this is a physical, presence-driven role
 ‚Ä¢ Ideally based in or able to travel to the Wiltshire region
 ‚Ä¢ Comfortable portraying a menacing, intense character

Project Details:
 ‚Ä¢ Filming Dates: Between 09/02/26 and 16/02/26
 ‚Ä¢ Unpaid role, but travel expenses (if applicable) and a copy of the finished film will be provided
 ‚Ä¢ The script is currently in progress, but I can provide a synopsis to anyone interested in learning more

# Statist*innen f√ºr neues YouTube-Dating-Format gesucht!

Was sagt der TikTok-Feed √ºber uns aus? Kann man dar√ºber entscheiden, ob man eine Person daten m√∂chte oder nicht?

F√ºr ein neues YouTube-Dating-Format sind wir auf der Suche nach Kandidat*innen, die herausfinden wollen, wie aussagekr√§ftig der digitale Fu√üabdruck f√ºr potentielle Dating-Partner*innen ist.

Du bist gerne auf Social Media, und du hast kein Problem damit, deinen Feed offenzulegen? Dann bewirb dich als Kandidat*in!

Bewirb dich jetzt als Single ‚Äì wir bewerten die Social-Feeds gemeinsam, du triffst deine Entscheidung!

Zeitraum: 10. + 11. Dezember (du musst nur an einem der beiden Drehtage Zeit haben)

**Three artist residencies in Sicily in 2026 for actors, artists, and writers ‚Äî now accepting applications**

Trinacria Theatre Company is thrilled to announce three artist residency opportunities for its milestone ten-year anniversary in 2026, inviting international creators to develop new work in the stunning rural landscape of Pezzolo:

**üåø PEZZOLO RETREAT RESIDENCY (NEW for 2026!)**
**May 12 ‚Äì June 1, 2026**
The company‚Äôs most flexible program to date, this 1, 2, or 3 week self-directed retreat invites artists of any discipline to immerse themselves in the quiet beauty of Pezzolo. Participants can dedicate uninterrupted time to an independent project or reconnect with their creative process without the expectation of a final showing.
**Applications due December 21.**
More information: www.trinacriatheatre.com/pezzolo-retreat-residency

**‚òÄÔ∏è TRINACRIA FESTIVAL RESIDENCY**
**July 24 ‚Äì August 13, 2026**
Designed for individual artists or small collectives developing work for presentation in the Trinacria Arts Festival, this residency blends independent practice with meaningful community engagement. Selected projects will reflect the festival‚Äôs vision and respond thoughtfully to the region‚Äôs landscape, culture, and audiences.
**Applications due December 21.**
More information: www.trinacriatheatre.com/trinacria-festival-residency

**‚úçÔ∏è PEZZOLO CREATIVE INTENSIVE FOR WRITERS: SCRIPT TRANSFORMATION**
**September 2026 (Exact dates TBA)**
Back by popular demand, this two-week workshop-residency supports writers ready to elevate a script or screenplay through focused development time and expert dramaturgical guidance. Led by award-winning Nigerian-American dramaturg Iyvon E. (Artistic Director of The Parsnip Ship; former Director of Artistic Programming at Signature Theatre), the program offers a rare, deeply supported environment for advancing a script to its next stage.
**Applications open January 2026.**

items.summary:
SINGING LESSONS ¬£60 hour

**First Session ¬£10! **

- West End credited performer with 4 University degrees in teaching and voice and music. YOUR LIE IN APRIL, FROZEN, CYRANO DE BERGERAC, EVITA, THE KING AND I.

-Teaching in London out of Dance Attic Studios Fulham Broadway @danceatticstudios and ONLINE.

- Got recurring technical problems? Have you ever been told that certain genres and songs are just not for you? That your voice will always be a certain way? Have you ever left a singing lesson confused?

- Join the hundreds who have deliberately and conscientiously tackled their technique, and start building confidence today.

- Clients tend to have graduated from 3 year programs and leave with fundamental holes in their technique that they now want to fill. Is that you?

BOOK at www.chrisfung.co.uk

Chris Fung - Singing Teacher

items.text: 1 month left to get your submissions in for ‚ÄúBe More Chill‚Äù The Musical!

sharedPost.text:
the wait is over! we are now accepting submissions for our summer production of ‚ÄúBe More Chill!‚Äù

for full details, visit the link in our bio.

Simone Nathalia - Director/Choreographer
Taylor McKee - Music Director
Madison Raybould - Choreographer
Morgan Da Silva-Rolph - Stage Manager

audition dates
in-person: December 20th & 21st, 2025
callbacks: January 3rd, 2026
self-tapes: submissions due on Dec. 19th

audition venue:
Carousel Theatre for Young People, 1411 Cartwright St, Granville Island

audition requirements:
all roles in this production are volunteer, non-union. xoxo welcomes performers 18+ of all genders, ethnicities, and skill levels to audition.

what to prepare:
1. 2 contrasting musical theatre songs, (you may only be asked to sing one, but please have both ready).

2. a 1-2 minute contemporary, comedic monologue - this must be memorized.

how to apply:
please email your headshot and resume to theatre@xoxotv.ca to be scheduled with an audition time, or to request a self-tape submission.

character breakdowns can be found in our ‚Äúaudition package‚Äù link in bio.

production dates:
July 15th - 18th, 2026

production venue:
Firehall Arts Centre, 280 E Cordova St, Vancouver

notes:
rehearsals will begin April 30th, 2026
Saturdays 10:00am to 6:00pm
Tuesdays & Thursdays 6:00pm to 10:00pm

contact info@xoxotv.ca or DM us with any questions!

best of luck to all performers - we‚Äôll see you at auditions! üòÅüíÑüêæ

Music and Lyrics by Joe Iconis
Book by Joe Tracz
Based on the Novel by Ned Vizzini

BE MORE CHILL is presented by arrangement with Concord Theatricals.
www.concordtheatricals.com
The world premiere production of Be More Chill was commissioned and originally produced by Two River Theater Company in Red Bank, NJ
John Dias, Artistic Director / Michael Hurst, Managing Director
This work was supported by a Theatre Commissioning and Production Initiative grant from the Doris Duke Charitable Foundation
Orchestrations and Arrangements by Charlie Rosen
.
.
.

It's been a while since I've organized an event, but I've partnered with Flink to host a low-key, yet vibrant gathering for brand ambassadors, influencers, content creators, actors, actresses, and film industry professionals. 

We'll be recognizing our viral stars who have exceeded 100k views on our campaigns. You or your clients could be honored next. If you have an interest in acting or aocial media marketing, content creation, film, this is for you!! For more information and to attend, click here.

https://forms.gle/GhutENbwc6vpXBLm9

Please note that attendance is limited to those in Houston or traveling, and RSVP registration is required. Feel free to bring a friend/associate. Acting in Longer Form ‚Äì with Arek Ziƒôtek

Ready to take your acting and improv to the next level and bring real stories to life on stage? This workshop is all about longer scenes, deeper characters, and authentic storytelling, guided by Arek Ziƒôtek, one of Warsaw‚Äôs most respected theatre improvisers and teachers.

Arek has worked with Keith Johnstone, the father of modern improvisation, and now he‚Äôs sharing that knowledge in this unique advanced workshop for experienced performers.

You‚Äôll explore long-form improvisation techniques, learn to build emotional depth in your characters, and discover how to create stories that feel real, funny, and moving, all in English.

üëâ Important: This is not for beginners. You‚Äôll need some previous acting or improv experience and a confident level of English. We‚Äôre keeping the group small so everyone gets space, feedback, and focus.

Why join?
‚ú® Learn from one of Poland‚Äôs top improv teachers.
‚ú® Master storytelling through longer scenes and strong relationships.
‚ú® Work in English with passionate, international performers.
‚ú® Grow your stage presence and confidence in a supportive circle.

Schedule & Pricing
üìÜ Starting: Tuesday, November 25th
‚è∞ 7:00 PM
üìç Atlas Tower ‚Äì al. Jerozolimskie 123A, Warsaw

üéüÔ∏è Limited Spots:
First 5 applicants: 300 PLN (full 4-week course)
Next 5 spots: 350 PLN

If more than 10 apply, we might open a second group, but no promises!

Join us for a deep, fun, and creative exploration of what it means to truly act and improvise in longer form.

Very Limited Spots https://fienta.com/pl/acting-storytelling-improv-workshop-with-arek-zietek-155700

items.text:
Hi Everyone! I run a nonprofit that provides children who have lost a parent or sibling with a special gift or experience to help them on their grief journey. In June 2026 we are hosting a 5-day free theater day-camp in Boulder for these bereaved children. We are partnering with an Atlanta-based theater company, Destination Theatre. If you or someone you know has a child who would qualify, please feel free to share this information with them. More info is on our website and application. Statistically 1 in 12 children will lose a parent or sibling by the time they are an adult so it is quite possible someone knows someone who would benefit from this experience.  I will be posting this in several groups, so you may see this again!

Take care!

If you or someone you know has a child who would qualify, please feel free to share this information with them. More info is on our website and application. Statistically 1 in 12 children will lose a parent or sibling by the time they are an adult so it is quite possible someone knows someone who would benefit from this experience.  I will be posting this in several groups, so you may see this again!

Take care!

items.text:
Science Boffins is currently looking for more phenomenal Science Boffins to help us to bring science to life for primary school children. We have schools booked during British Science Week which runs from 9th to 13th March as well as party/events throughout the year.

You don't need a formal background in science as we teach you everything you'll need to know.

All you need is access to a car (unless London based), the ability to work some weekends/weekdays and the desire to launch rockets, concoct potions and generally share just how much fun science can be.

HOW DOES BEING A SCIENCE BOFFIN WORK?

For the right person, this could be the most fun way of making an extra income.

You'll get to enjoy inspiring and educating children, having a fantastic time and getting paid along the way. You'll travel to an event in your local area and bring science to life for primary school age children with some brilliant science experiments.

Are you a fun, enthusiastic and reliable person and able to communicate effectively and promptly to potential bookings? Then join a nationwide team of 40+ well-paid Science Boffin presenters.  We have a strong reputation, rave reviews, and the privilege of working with some globally recognised companies.

We're a friendly bunch and have a (we think!) cracking training program to help you get up to speed. If that sounds like you? You too can become one of our amazing Science Boffins and bring science alive to children.

Looking forward to hearing from you.

Annette

Science Boffins

All you need is access to a car (unless London based), the ability to work some weekends/weekdays and the desire to launch rockets, concoct potions and generally share just how much fun science can be.

HOW DOES BEING A SCIENCE BOFFIN WORK?

For the right person, this could be the most fun way of making an extra income.

You'll get to enjoy inspiring and educating children, having a fantastic time and getting paid along the way. You'll travel to an event in your local area and bring science to life for primary school age children with some brilliant science experiments.

Are you a fun, enthusiastic and reliable person and able to communicate effectively and promptly to potential bookings? Then join a nationwide team of 40+ well-paid Science Boffin presenters.  We have a strong reputation, rave reviews, and the privilege of working with some globally recognised companies.

We're a friendly bunch and have a (we think!) cracking training program to help you get up to speed. If that sounds like you? You too can become one of our amazing Science Boffins and bring science alive to children.

Looking forward to hearing from you.

Annette

Science Boffins
items.title: Science Boffins is currently looking for more phenomenal Science Boffins to help us to bring science to life for primary school children. We have schools booked during British Science Week which runs from 9th to 13th March as well as party/events throughout the year.

items.text:
Hello All,
We are looking for an **actor for creative UGC** (User-Generated Content) to produce engaging, relatable, and authentic video content for Helmit, a parental control app designed to protect children from harassment, predators, and cyberbullying online. Our AI analyzes social media activity privately on the device and alerts parents only when there is a potential threat. Our mission is to educate families about online safety, cyberbullying, and protecting kids in the digital world.

**Who We Are Looking For**

- Parent, preferably female, age 35 or above

- English speaking preferred, German possible as well

- Comfortable speaking on camera

- Able to create warm, natural, storytelling style content

- A parent who understands real challenges in raising kids today

- Being a parent would be perfect, but not absolutely necessary

- Ideally located in Munich or the surrounding area

- 1 day of filming

**Topics include**

- Parenting education

- Parenting stories and experiences

- Light, natural mentions of our app when relevant

- scripts will be provided by us

- You may adjust the script wording to match your tone, voice, and natural speaking style

- You do not need to involve your kids. We want great parents to be part of the project, not the children

All content will be posted by our team on Helmit‚Äôs various social media channels

**What We Value**

Our main goal is to work closely with parents so we can better understand real challenges, create relatable educational content, and continue building our product to support families more effectively.

**Application - **Please include

- Samples of your previous video work

- A brief introduction about yourself and your parenting experience

If you love storytelling, creating honest content, and want to help build a safer digital world for kids, we would love to work with you. Please contact via email: [Niklas@helmit.org](mailto:Niklas@helmit.org)

More information about us: [www.helmit.org](http://www.helmit.org)

Hello everyone! My name is Sofia Vargas and I‚Äôm the Producer for the UNCSA third year film, *Metanoia*. We are casting our lead characters!

Story: On the last night of Mariana‚Äôs visit to her brother Mateo in the U.S., the two Latin American siblings are pushed into unfamiliar territory when a moment of discovery at a Latin club gives Mariana a glimpse of who she truly is. Together, they navigate the fragile, unspoken shifts in identity, desire, and growing up that both pull them apart and draw them closer.

We are accepting auditions submissions! Character Breakdowns are attached. If you‚Äôre interested in auditioning for these roles, send your **name, age, pronouns,** **headshot, and role preference  **to [metanoiafilmcasting@gmail.com](mailto:metanoiafilmcasting@gmail.com) for audition materials!

Together, they navigate the fragile, unspoken shifts in identity, desire, and growing up that both pull them apart and draw them closer.

We are accepting auditions submissions! Character Breakdowns are attached. If you‚Äôre interested in auditioning for these roles, send your **name, age, pronouns,** **headshot, and role preference  **to [metanoiafilmcasting@gmail.com](mailto:metanoiafilmcasting@gmail.com) for audition materials! 

The **interest deadline **is December 1st! 

Production title: Metanoia 

Union / Non-Union: Non-Union 

Paid / Not Paid: Not Paid

Production Type: Student Film

Production Company: University of North Carolina School of the Arts (School of Filmmaking)

Director: Mart√≠n Collo Sastoque 

Producer: Sofia Vargas

Audition Type: In Person Auditions

Filming: January and February 2026

Shooting Location: Winston-Salem, NC

Email: [metanoiafilmcasting@gmail.com](mailto:metanoiafilmcasting@gmail.com)

We look forward to seeing your audition!

**CASTING CALL ‚Äî Vancouver, BC**
Looking for actors (18+) to play *16‚Äì18* for a 4th-year Capilano University short film titled **BOYISH**.

A coming-of-age story about the messy shift from boyhood to adulthood, dumb dares, and the people we meet along the way.

**ROLES:**
**LUKA (lead)** ‚Äî male-presenting, playing 16‚Äì18. Quiet, awkward, observant.
**YAZ (lead)** ‚Äî male-presenting, playing 16‚Äì18. Bright, restless, warm.

**Union + Non-Union welcome (volunteer)**
**Filming:** Feb 7‚Äì9, 2026 (Vancouver)
**Actors must be 18+**

To submit, send headshot + reel to **boyish2026@gmail.com** by **Dec 1st, 2025 ‚Äì 11:59pm**.
Subject line: **BOYISH ‚Äì LUKA** or **BOYISH ‚Äì YAZ**

üìÖ Casting Day: 11th December - London

üí•What You Bring
An awesome personality, strong communication and a passion for creating amazing guest experiences. Entertainment experience is great but character is everything.

* Discounted on-site food
* A team that feels like a tribe

Making Contact!

Selling out very quickly!
Only two spaces left.
Male identifying Actors encouraged. 

www.mindbodyvoice.co.uk

Making Contact is a twelve-week physical theatre workshop that asks: How do performers make contact? How is it managed? How can actors prepare for physical, violent, or intimate scenes?

This playful yet practical course provides a safe, yet brave space to build confidence and skill in physical connection.

Explore consent and boundary-setting practices, alongside dynamic exercises like gameplay, contact improvisation and shared weight work designed to build confidence toward physical contact.

Led by a certified fight and intimacy director with over over 30 years‚Äô international experience, Making Contact is ideal for actors looking to set healthy boundaries, overcome nervousness around contact, or explore and extend their outer personal edges of physical performance. It offers practical tools for theatre and film while fostering trust, openness, and joy in the craft.

items.text:
Hey, listen ‚Äî if you‚Äôve ever sat in a rehearsal, thought about your objective, asked yourself ‚ÄúWhat would I do if I were in this situation?‚Äù or chased some kind of ‚Äútruth‚Äù in a scene, guess what? You‚Äôre already using Stanislavski. Yeah, I said it. You‚Äôve been dabbling in his psychological period without even realizing it. But here‚Äôs the thing: it actually comes from a really specific moment in theatre history, and knowing that makes your work feel even smarter.

Back in 1912, Stanislavski founded the First Studio at the Moscow Art Theatre. This wasn‚Äôt just a fancy acting class ‚Äî it was the first professional actor training lab connected to a real theatre company. Think of it as a playground for actors to experiment, fail, and discover the System under the guidance of serious mentors. The artistic head was Leopold Sulerzhitsky, the moral compass of the Studio, while Stanislavski himself came by regularly to teach, guide, and supervise experiments. This is where the psychological period of his system really took shape ‚Äî a system all about understanding the inner life of a role and actually experiencing it on stage, not just ‚Äúperforming it.‚Äù

Some of the actors from the First Studio went on to take these ideas around the world. Yevgeny Vakhtangov blended imagination and psychological truth; Michael Chekhov created the Psycho-Physical approach that Hollywood would later eat up; Richard Boleslavsky brought the system to America and trained Strasberg, Adler, and Meisner; and Maria Ouspenskaya co-founded the American Laboratory Theatre and became a legendary teacher. If you‚Äôve studied any modern acting technique in English, you‚Äôre feeling the ripple effects of these people.

So what are you actually doing when you work on objectives, given circumstances, the ‚ÄúMagic If‚Äù, emotional memory, or imagination? You‚Äôre right there in the middle of the psychological period of Stanislavski‚Äôs evolution. This is exactly what the First Studio trained actors to do ‚Äî explore the inner life of a role and live truthfully on stage. And this isn‚Äôt just theoretical ‚Äî it became the foundation for Method Acting, Adler‚Äôs imaginative approach, Meisner‚Äôs ‚Äúliving truthfully,‚Äù and almost every technique you see taught in English today.

Why does this matter now? Because knowing this history gives you context. You understand that Stanislavski didn‚Äôt have ‚Äúone system.‚Äù He evolved over forty years, and what most actors learn today is only one slice of his genius. By understanding where your rehearsal work comes from, you can make smarter, more grounded choices on stage and connect what you‚Äôre doing to a real lineage of practice.

If you want to dive deeper, there‚Äôs a treasure trove out there. Stanislavski‚Äôs autobiography, newly retranslated by Jean Benedetti, gives a modern, precise view of his terminology ‚Äî none of the old Americanized shortcuts. Anatoli Smiliansky has invaluable material interpreting the System. And the Lust for Life documentary shows the Moscow Art Theatre in action, giving a contemporary view on how Stanislavski‚Äôs work actually looked in practice. All of it connects what you‚Äôre doing in rehearsal to the real history behind it.

Bottom line: you‚Äôve been using Stanislavski your whole acting life, whether you knew it or not. But now you know the roots ‚Äî the First Studio, the psychological period, the actors who carried it around the world. It‚Äôs all there, and it‚Äôs all part of why your objectives, imagination, and inner work actually work.

But here‚Äôs the thing: it actually comes from a really specific moment in theatre history, and knowing that makes your work feel even smarter.

Back in 1912, Stanislavski founded the First Studio at the Moscow Art Theatre. This wasn‚Äôt just a fancy acting class ‚Äî it was the first professional actor training lab connected to a real theatre company. Think of it as a playground for actors to experiment, fail, and discover the System under the guidance of serious mentors. The artistic head was Leopold Sulerzhitsky, the moral compass of the Studio, while Stanislavski himself came by regularly to teach, guide, and supervise experiments. This is where the psychological period of his system really took shape ‚Äî a system all about understanding the inner life of a role and actually experiencing it on stage, not just ‚Äúperforming it.‚Äù

Some of the actors from the First Studio went on to take these ideas around the world. Yevgeny Vakhtangov blended imagination and psychological truth; Michael Chekhov created the Psycho-Physical approach that Hollywood would later eat up; Richard Boleslavsky brought the system to America and trained Strasberg, Adler, and Meisner; and Maria Ouspenskaya co-founded the American Laboratory Theatre and became a legendary teacher. If you‚Äôve studied any modern acting technique in English, you‚Äôre feeling the ripple effects of these people.

So what are you actually doing when you work on objectives, given circumstances, the ‚ÄúMagic If‚Äù, emotional memory, or imagination? You‚Äôre right there in the middle of the psychological period of Stanislavski‚Äôs evolution. This is exactly what the First Studio trained actors to do ‚Äî explore the inner life of a role and live truthfully on stage. And this isn‚Äôt just theoretical ‚Äî it became the foundation for Method Acting, Adler‚Äôs imaginative approach, Meisner‚Äôs ‚Äúliving truthfully,‚Äù and almost every technique you see taught in English today.

Why does this matter now? Because knowing this history gives you context. You understand that Stanislavski didn‚Äôt have ‚Äúone system.‚Äù He evolved over forty years, and what most actors learn today is only one slice of his genius. By understanding where your rehearsal work comes from, you can make smarter, more grounded choices on stage and connect what you‚Äôre doing to a real lineage of practice.

If you want to dive deeper, there‚Äôs a treasure trove out there. Stanislavski‚Äôs autobiography, newly retranslated by Jean Benedetti, gives a modern, precise view of his terminology ‚Äî none of the old Americanized shortcuts. Anatoli Smiliansky has invaluable material interpreting the System. And the Lust for Life documentary shows the Moscow Art Theatre in action, giving a contemporary view on how Stanislavski‚Äôs work actually looked in practice. All of it connects what you‚Äôre doing in rehearsal to the real history behind it.

Bottom line: you‚Äôve been using Stanislavski your whole acting life, whether you knew it or not. But now you know the roots ‚Äî the First Studio, the psychological period, the actors who carried it around the world. It‚Äôs all there, and it‚Äôs all part of why your objectives, imagination, and inner work actually work.

VANCOUVER CREATORS ‚Äî CASTING NOW üé¨

Fourth Frame Media is making a bold new social series that explores identity, groupthink, and how we judge others. If you‚Äôre vibrant, curious, and outspoken, we want you on camera. Filming is in Vancouver, BC (local talent only).

Volunteer-based, and the winner takes home a prize.

Topics we‚Äôre shooting:

* Do I Look Like My Job?

* Best Friend Chooses Your Partner ‚Äî Person Seeking Partner

* Is the Canadian Dream Still Alive?

* Match 30 people to their jobs

* Can People Match Your Income to You?

Apply here: https://www.4thframemedia.com/casting

Please share with friends in Vancouver who‚Äôd love this!

items.text:
**CASTING CALL: LIVE SHOW HOSTS**

Los Angeles (Hollywood Studio)

**Firework** is seeking energetic, camera-ready **Live Show Hosts** to lead interactive livestream product demonstrations!

**PAY:** $25-$40/hour (based on experience)

**ROLE DETAILS:**
* Host live product shows from our Hollywood, CA studio
* Present tech & lifestyle products in an authentic, conversational style
* Work as freelance/1099 with potential to transition to part-time employee
* Average 5-10 hours/week (rarely exceeds 15 hours)
* Mostly weekdays, 8 AM - 8 PM PT

**WE'RE LOOKING FOR:**
* Strong on-camera presence & natural speaking ability
* Reliable, punctual, professional
* Available weekdays during business hours
* Prior hosting/livestream/UGC/acting experience preferred but not required

**AUDITION OPTIONS:**

**Option 1: On-Site Audition**
* Dates: December 10-11, 2025
* Time: 10 AM - 1 PM PT
* 10-15 min audition (3-min one-take hosting scenario)

**Option 2: Self-Tape Submission**
* Deadline: December 11, 2025 (11:59 PM PT)
* 3 minutes, vertical, one continuous take
* Host any tech/electronic product as if live
* Email to: Kimmy@fireworkhq.com
* Subject: [Your Name] ‚Äì Live Show Host Submission - LA Digital Showroom Host - Self Tape Submission

**CASTING CALL: LIVE SHOW HOSTS**

Los Angeles (Hollywood Studio)

**Firework** is seeking energetic, camera-ready **Live Show Hosts** to lead interactive livestream product demonstrations!

**PAY:** $25-$40/hour (based on experience)

**ROLE DETAILS:**
* Host live product shows from our Hollywood, CA studio
* Present tech & lifestyle products in an authentic, conversational style
* Work as freelance/1099 with potential to transition to part-time employee
* Average 5-10 hours/week (rarely exceeds 15 hours)
* Mostly weekdays, 8 AM - 8 PM PT

**WE'RE LOOKING FOR:**
* Strong on-camera presence & natural speaking ability
* Reliable, punctual, professional
* Available weekdays during business hours
* Prior hosting/livestream/UGC/acting experience preferred but not required

* Dates: December 10-11, 2025

Now casting couples in mixed orientation relationships for a new documentary series with a major cable network.

Mixed orientation relationships, often known as lavender partnerships, involve two partners who differ in their sexual orientation. We want to hear from couples who live together, share a daily life, and are engaged, married, or soon to be engaged.

This series will explore how couples navigate identity, commitment, outside expectations, and the realities of loving in a way that challenges societal norms.

If this describes you or someone you know, you can share your story at the link below.

mixedorientationcasting.castingcrane.com
